Key Match Events: Chicago took advantage of two Nats errors to create three extra runs that proved to be the difference in this one.
Their defense also erased two Washington runners on the basepaths.
Post-Match Reflections: The Cubs went 18-8 in the month of August, digging them out of the hole they were in after a disastrous May and June.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Cubs look for their second straight sweep Sunday at 12:35pm CT.
Jordan Wicks is back from injury to take on Mitchell Parker in a matchup available on Marquee and 670 The Score.
